    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Viguiera quinqueradiata are fever, which is reduced due to its anti-inflammatory properties, and bronchitis, a condition that benefits from its expectorant activity, allowing mucus to be expelled more easily. Additionally, Viguiera quinqueradiata has been shown to exhibit antifungal properties, effectively treating fungal infections, such as candidiasis, and its antimicrobial activity also makes it effective against bacterial infections like pneumonia. Furthermore, Viguiera quinqueradiata has been found to reduce swelling and pain associated with conditions like arthritis, thanks to its anti-inflammatory properties, and its antioxidant activity helps to protect against cell damage caused by free radicals, which can contribute to the development of various diseases, including cancer. Its antiseptic properties also make it effective in treating skin conditions like acne and dermatitis. Moreover, Viguiera quinqueradiata has been used to treat gastrointestinal disorders like diarrhea and dysentery, which are often caused by bacterial or viral infections.",
