    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Viguiera quinqueradiata are flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol, which have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. These compounds have been found to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, thereby reducing inflammation and oxidative stress. The plant also contains sesquiterpenes like quinqueroside and quinquercin, which have been demonstrated to exhibit antimicrobial and anti-cancer activities. Additionally, Viguiera quinqueradiata contains phenolic acids including ferulic and sinapic acids, which have been reported to have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects. These bioactive compounds work synergistically to provide the medicinal properties of Viguiera quinqueradiata, supporting its use in traditional medicine for various health conditions.",
