    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Viguiera quinqueradiata are infusion, tea, tincture, salve, and decoction. Infusion and tea are typically used to make a beverage, often with the leaves, stems, or flowers of the plant steeped in hot water, while tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the plant in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin. A salve is a topical preparation made by infusing the plant in oil, which is then applied to the skin to treat conditions such as wounds or skin irritations. Decoction is a preparation made by boiling the plant in water to extract the soluble compounds, which can be used as a treatment for various health conditions. These preparations are often used in traditional medicine to treat conditions such as digestive issues, fever, and skin problems due to the plant's reported anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties.",
